               <p>
                  <persName id="t18420404-name-1230" type="witnessName">
                     <interp inst="t18420404-name-1230" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420404-name-1230" type="surname" value="BOWLING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420404-name-1230" type="given" value="AMELIA"></interp>AMELIA BOWLING</persName>. I am a widow, and live at No. 17, Cardington-place, Hampstead-road. On the 31st of March, about nine o'clock, or a quarter past, in the evening, I was passing through Wigmore-street—I felt some one touch my side, and a drag at my dress—I saw the prisoner at my side—I put my hand to my pocket, where I had my purse and some keys—the prisoner had one end of the purse in his hand—I caught hold of the other end of it—he pulled it through my fingers, and got it, then turned and ran away down a mews close by—I pursued him, and saw him taken, without losing sight of him—I had some silver at one end of my purse, and four sovereigns at the other—I heard some money fall on the stones as he turned round again to meet me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you get your gold again? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, I did not pick it up, because I could not see it—I did not see the prisoner's face at the time he took it—his head was down—he was close to me—I pursued him down the mews, and saw him taken—I am quite sure he is the man—Bowling is not my husband's name—I do not like to tell his name—I was christened Amelia Bowling—they are my two Christian names—I have gone by that name for the last twelve months, and took a house in that name—I have been told that my husband is dead, but I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184204040209"></xptr>
               <p>never made any inquiries—it is three or four years since I saw him—I am under the protection of my friends—I am not living with any one to whom I am not married—I live by myself and daughter and servants—I have had lodgers—I have property to live on, money advanced me by a rela<lb></lb>tion—I do not wish to tell any more—I understand my husband died in America about two years ago—my maiden name was Nicholas—a stranger informed me of my husband's death, and said the family were in mourning—I saw none of the family myself—I would rather be excused saying under what circumstances my husband went away—I had much rather he did not return—the person who informed me of his death came from Maid-stone, where the family was residing.</p>
               <p>
